    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Hooker.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>The Books arrived quite safely this morning.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Emma desires her thanks to M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Hooker for her note, but she is sorry she thought of troubling herself about the socks.</p>
<p>I will do D. Candolle first, as I guess that most likely to be wanted: the job will be a long one.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I am very glad to have R. Brown’s Prodromus.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Whenever I try the Labiatæ in different ways, which will not be soon, you shall hear the result, as I shall wish much to tell it.</p>
<p>Thanks for Dana’s pamphlet:<ref target="#foot.f5"/> I am much disappointed in it. I have high respect for Dana, but in this brochure “I do not think he is much of a Baconian philosopher,” as our friend J. E. Gray says.— I hate such far-fetched analogies, as comparing an atom of oxygen with a living being.— I believe, poor fellow, he believes in 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> Ch<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. of Genesis, so great allowances must be made for him.<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>I have been reading in proof Sheets Huxley’s “Explanatory Catalogue” &amp; it seems to me quite an admirable, but very brief, resume on the Natural Sciences<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p>
<p>I am very sorry to hear that you do not intend to give generalisations in your Tasmanian Introduction, but I do not believe you will be able to resist: what is in the spirit must come out.<ref target="#foot.f8"/></p>
<p>I hope that poor dear Henslow is going on well.—</p>
<p>Ever yours | C. Darwin</p>
<p>I have just finished a tremendous job, my chapter on Hybridism: it has taken me 3 months to write, after all facts collected together!<ref target="#foot.f9"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">3.1 that] <hi rend="italic">interl after del illeg</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

